# Separating Departures vs. Arrivals

We only predict departures from PIT. Arrivals are kept separately — they're
useful later for features like "was the inbound plane late?"

```{r split-dep-arr}
# departures only, years combined
train <- bind_rows(
  flights_2023 |> filter(origin == "PIT") |> mutate(data_year = 2023),
  flights_2024 |> filter(origin == "PIT") |> mutate(data_year = 2024)
)

# arrivals saved for potential feature engineering
arrivals_train <- bind_rows(
  flights_2023 |> filter(dest == "PIT") |> mutate(data_year = 2023),
  flights_2024 |> filter(dest == "PIT") |> mutate(data_year = 2024)
)

# test splits
test_visible <- flights_test_visible |> filter(origin == "PIT")
test_guess   <- flights_test_guess   |> filter(origin == "PIT")

cat("train:", nrow(train), "| test_visible:", nrow(test_visible),
    "| test_guess:", nrow(test_guess),
    "| arrivals (for features):", nrow(arrivals_train), "\n")
```

